race.comment: SCULPTOR (2) switched from the Portelli yard, beaten 2.6L at Port Macquarie as a $2.20 favourite. Brought compelling form to that and has been kept up to the mark with a trial since. Maps well and with Bullock staying aboard he can make amends. GRASSBURN (3) was quickly on track, narrowly missing at Port Macquarie. He's switched from Victoria's premier stable and fitter rates to be right in it. OCEAN JOY (1) peaks and is knocking on the door. Is still well shy of her best and gets in well with the 3kg claim. DEEBEE'S GIRL (7) is lightly raced and went close here first-up before delivering his Maiden easily at Kempsey, leading again. Jumps from the inside gate and will give a big sight in tougher grade.
